Always with present progessive

We can use always together with the present progressive to talk about something that irritates or annoys us.

I can't believe I'm always losing my keys. 
(I'm upset that I lose my keys all the time)

She's always shouting at me.
(I'm angry that she shouts at me all the time)

You are always going on about your salary.

He told me I'm always forgetting to say hello.

It's always snowing on my birthday.

